{
  "text": "2M KCl and saturated CaSO 4 were used to extract ammonium and nitrate nitrogen respectively and the ratio between soil and extract was 1:5. Shaking end-over-end for 1 h filtered and determined nitrogen concentrations by using a Cleverchem200 auto analyzer (Dechem-Tect Germany). Noted that the filtered samples were stored in a refrigerator at 4\u00baC if analysis was to be within 10 days. If there was a longer delay, samples were immediately frozen at -5\u00baC and then defrosted at 4\u00baC prior to analysis [CITATION_1] .",
